com.hazelcast.util.collection

Class InternalSetMultimap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.util.collection.InternalSetMultimap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K -
    V - 

    public class InternalSetMultimap<K,V>
extends Object
    Simplistic implementation of MultiMap. It's not thread-safe, concurrent access has to be externally synchronized. It does not allow duplicates: The same value can be associated with the same key once only. Duplicates are eliminated. The name has a prefix Internal- to avoid confusion with MultiMap
